      • sendMessageToAll

        public java.lang.String sendMessageToAll(UserManager userManager,
                                         ConversationManager conversationManager,
                                         java.lang.String content,
                                         UserType group)
        A method for sending a message to all users of a certain type (either Attendee or Speaker). Should only be accessible by organizers. Returns a string representation of whether the message was successfully sent.
        Parameters:
        userManager - The UserManager to use.
        conversationManager - The ConversationManager to use.
        content - The content of the message as a String.
        group - The type of user that will be receiving the message.
        Returns:
        Whether the message was successfully sent.

      • createNewEvent

        public java.lang.String createNewEvent(RoomManager roomManager,
                                       EventsManager eventsManager,
                                       UserManager userManager,
                                       ConversationManager conversationManager,
                                       java.lang.String name,
                                       java.time.LocalDateTime time,
                                       java.util.UUID roomId,
                                       java.util.HashSet<java.util.UUID> speakerId,
                                       int capacity,
                                       int duration,
                                       java.util.List<RoomFeatures> features)
        Method that lets organizers create new events.
        Parameters:
        roomManager - The RoomManager to use.
        eventsManager - The EventsManager to use.
        userManager - The UserManager to use.
        conversationManager - The ConversationManager to use.
        name - The name of the new event
        time - Time of the new event
        roomId - UUID of the room of the new event
        speakerId - An HashSet of UUID where each UUID represents a unique speaker of the new event
        capacity - an Integer object that represents the maximum number of attendees allowed in the event
        duration - an Integer object represents the number of hours that the event will last. All events can only last increment in hours.
        features - a list of RoomFeatures objects where each represent a feature that is required for the event
        Returns:
        A String representing the status of the creation of the event.

      • addNewRooms

        public java.util.UUID addNewRooms(RoomManager roomManager,
                                  java.lang.String name,
                                  int capacity,
                                  int earliestStartTime,
                                  int closingTime)
        Method that lets organizers add new rooms to the system and returns the added room id.
        Parameters:
        roomManager - The RoomManager to use.
        name - name of the new room
        capacity - an Integer object that represents the maximum allowed attendees in the room
        earliestStartTime - integer object that represents in a 24 hour clock cycle when an event can be scheduled at this room everyday.
        closingTime - integer object that represents in a 24 hour clock cycle when an event must end in this room everyday.
        Returns:
        return the new Room Id

      • changeEventCapacity

        public java.lang.String changeEventCapacity(EventsManager eventsManager,
                                            java.util.UUID eventID,
                                            int capacity)
        Change event's capacity if the number of attendees in the event is less than or equal to the given new capacity.
        Parameters:
        eventsManager - The EventsManager to use.
        eventID - UUID object that represents the event that capacity will be changed
        capacity - Integer object that represents the new maximum number of attendees allowed. Must be greater than 0.
        Returns:
        A String representing the status of changing the event capacity.
